      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED LIGHT RACHEL (8) finished a solid third on debut, then worked hard from a poor draw with a fading sixth over 1300m at Canberra. Has the addition of blinkers and will prove hard to catch from the good barrier. MILK FOAM (7) back in grade fourth-up and shapes as the main danger despite drawing out again. Snagged back from the poor gate and failed to get into the contest when a dismal eighth over 900m at Newcastle. Found to be (2/5) lame in the near-foreleg at latest. Deserves another chance in this grade. IVORY FROST (6) raced closer to the speed when a most improved second  over 1100m at Goulburn in the soft (7) going. Near her top for this and stays in the mix. HELLFIRE HENRY (1) Pariah gelding from Bo Rossa on debut for the Jarrod Austin yard. Has shown enough in his two recent trials and gets map favours.",
